The '''2008 Milan–San Remo''' [[cycling race]] took place on March 22, 2008, and was won by [[Fabian Cancellara]]. It was the 99th edition of the [[Milan–San Remo]] [[classic cycle races|monument classic]]. It was three&nbsp;kilometres longer than 2007, at 298&nbsp;km, following the addition of the Le Mànie climb, which was due to roadworks along the previously planned route. The race concluded on Lungomare Italo Calvino and not on the traditional Via Roma due to construction and the Easter weekend.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://autobus.cyclingnews.com/news.php?id=news/2008/mar08/mar06news2 |title='Maniac' enters Milano-San Remo |date=2008-03-06 |accessdate=2008-03-21 |work=cyclingnews.com}}</ref>

[[2007 Milan–San Remo|Last year's]] winner [[Óscar Freire]] was the favourite with bookmakers, following his recent double stage victory at the [[2008 Tirreno–Adriatico|Tirreno–Adriatico]].<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.unibet.co.uk/betting/cycling/milano---sanremo%7C1000093233,1000093633.odds |title=Cycling/Milano - San Remo |publisher=Unibet |accessdate=2008-03-21}}</ref>

