{{Infobox handball club| |clubname=Akureyri Handboltafélag |image= |fullname=Akureyri Handboltafélag |short name=Akureyri |founded=2006 |ground=Íþróttahöllin á Akureyri |capacity=1110 |chairman=Þorsteinn Hlynur Jónsson |manager=[[Sverre Andreas Jakobsson|Sverre Jakobsson]] |league=[[Úrvalsdeild karla (handball)|Úrvalsdeild karla]] |season= |position= |website=https://akureyrihandbolti.is |colour1=black |colour2=black |leftarm1=000000 |body1=000000 |rightarm1=000000 |shorts1=000000 |leftarm2=000000 |body2=000000 |rightarm2=000000 |shorts2=000000 }}
'''Akureyri Handboltafélag''' is a men's [[Team handball|handball]] club, located in [[Akureyri]], [[Iceland]].
==History== Akureyri Handboltafélag was founded in 2006 as a joint team between [[Knattspyrnufélag Akureyrar|KA]] and [[Þór Akureyri]]. In 2011 it posted the best record in the [[Úrvalsdeild karla (handball)|Úrvalsdeild karla]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Akureyri deildarmeistari |url=http://www.visir.is/section/MEDIA99&fileid=VTVFEF16DEF-BD67-42B4-B2A3-17C6A3CC1E96 |accessdate=25 July 2018 |work=[[Vísir.is]] |date=29 March 2011 |language=Icelandic}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author1=Ívar Benediktsson |title=Akureyri er deildarmeistari |url=https://www.mbl.is/frettir/forsida/2011/03/28/akureyri_er_deildarmeistari/ |accessdate=25 July 2018 |work=[[Morgunblaðið]] |date=28 March 2011 |language=Icelandic}}</ref> It made it to the 2011 Úrvalsdeild finals where it lost to [[FH Hafnarfjördur|FH]] in front of a record crowd of 2950 people in [[Kaplakriki]].<ref>{{cite news|title=FH Íslandsmeistari|url=http://www.ruv.is/frett/fh-islandsmeistari|accessdate=11 February 2018|work=[[RÚV]]|date=4 May 2011|language=Icelandic}}</ref>
In 2017, the club was relegated from the Úrvalsdeild.<ref>{{cite news |author1=Arnar Geir Halldórsson |title=Akureyri átt handboltalið í efstu deild síðustu 33 ár |url=http://www.kaffid.is/akureyri-att-handboltalid-efstu-deild-sidustu-33-ar/ |accessdate=25 July 2018 |work=kaffid.is |date=4 April 2017 |language=Icelandic}}</ref> and shortly after, KA decided to break off from the cooperation and fielded their own team starting from 2017-2018. Þór continued to run its men's team under the Akureyri name<ref>{{cite news |title=Akureyri handboltafélag tekur þátt |url=https://www.mbl.is/sport/handbolti/2017/05/15/akureyri_handboltafelag_tekur_thatt/ |accessdate=25 July 2018 |work=[[Morgunblaðið]] |date=15 May 2017 |language=Icelandic}}</ref> and in 2018, the team finished first in [[1. deild karla (football)|1. deild karla]] and was promoted back to the Úrvalsdeild along with KA, which finished second.<ref>{{cite news |title=Akureyri aftur upp í efstu deild |url=https://www.mbl.is/sport/handbolti/2018/03/23/akureyri_aftur_upp_i_efstu_deild/ |accessdate=25 July 2018 |work=[[Morgunblaðið]] |date=23 March 2018 |language=Icelandic}}</ref>
== Trophies == '''[[1. deild karla (handball)|1. deild karla]]''': * 2018
