{{Infobox Sport governing body |assocname= Integrated Cycling Federation of the Philippines |abbrev = PhilCycling |sport= [[Cycling (sport)|Cycling]] |category = |image = |image_size= |caption = |jurisdiction = |founded = |aff = |affdate = |region_served= Philippines |headquarters = |location = |president = |chiefexec = |secretary = |coach = |womenscoach = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = |year closed = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = |countryflag=Philippines |countryflag2= }} The '''Integrated Cycling Federation of the Philippines''' (PhilCycling) is the national [[Sport governing body|governing body]] for [[cycling]] as a sport{{citation needed|date=September 2016}} in the [[Philippines]]. It is duly recognised by the [[Philippine Sports Commission]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.web.psc.gov.ph/|title=Philippine Sports Commission|website=www.web.psc.gov.ph|access-date=2016-09-04}}</ref> and the [[Philippine Olympic Committee]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://olympic.ph/|title=Philippine Olympic Committee|last=Sumagui|first=Kamilla|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> and the [[Union Cycliste Internationale|International Cycling Union (Union Cycliste Internationale a.k.a. UCI)]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.uci.ch|title=Union Cycliste Internationale|website=www.uci.ch|access-date=2016-09-04}}</ref>
The Federation houses the four (4) Olympic Cycling disciplines: * [[Road cycling|Road Cycling]] * [[Mountain bike racing|Mountain Bike Racing]] ** [[Cross-country cycling|Cross Country Olympic]] (XCO) ** [[Downhill mountain biking|Downhill Mountain Bike Racing]] (DHI) * [[Track cycling|Track Cycling]] * [[BMX racing|BMX Racing]]
