{{Infobox Korean name | img = Seoul Student Gymnasium.jpg | caption = Jamsil Students' Gymnasium | hangul = 잠실학생체육관 | hanja = {{linktext|蠶|室|學|生|體|育|館}} | rr = Jamsil Haksaeng Che-yukgwan | mr = Chamsil Haksaeng Ch'eyukkwan |}} '''Jamsil Students' Gymnasium''' ({{ko-hhrm|잠실학생체육관|蠶室學生體育館}}) is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] located in [[Seoul, South Korea]]. The capacity of the arena is 7,500 and was built from November 1972 to December 1976 to host [[Boxing at the 1988 Summer Olympics|Boxing]] events at the [[1988 Summer Olympics]], and wheelchair basketball events at the [[1988 Summer Paralympics]].
==Events== Jamsil has held a number of [[Esports]] events, including the [[StarCraft]] competitions the [http://wiki.teamliquid.net/starcraft/10th_SonicTV_Starleague|2015 10th SonicTV Starleague] and [http://wiki.teamliquid.net/starcraft/2012_Tving_OSL|2012 Tving OSL].
PWF Korea Life Attack Pro wrestling event will be held on April 27, 2014 at this venue. A historical moment in Korean culture history as a lost sport has regained its popularity in this country. Aside from the Olympics, it also hosted boxing events at the [[1986 Asian Games]], and is the home stadium for the [[Seoul SK Knights]] of the [[Korean Basketball League]].
On 15 March 2012, general cable broadcaster [[JTBC]] held a public shoot and press conference at the Gymnasium, to showcase their new programme ''[[Shinhwa Broadcast]]'', hosted by six-member boyband [[Shinhwa]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Kim|first=Ji-yeon|title=Shinhwa on ''Shinhwa Broadcast''|url=http://global.mnet.com/news/newsdetail.m?searchNewsVO.news_id=201203161015_4386|accessdate=12 November 2012|newspaper=Mnet News|date=16 March 2012|agency=CJ E&M}}</ref>
