'''Pakistan Automobiles Corporation''' (sometimes abbreviated to '''PACO''')<ref>See, for example, ''[[Wisden Cricketers' Almanack|Wisden]]'' 1994, pp. 1219-23.</ref> were a [[first-class cricket]] side that played in the [[Patron's Trophy]], the [[Quaid-e-Azam Trophy]] and the [[Pentangular Trophy]] between 1983–84 and 1993-94. Their most successful era was in the early 1980s under the captaincy of [[Shahid Mahboob]].
In all they played 83 first-class matches, with 20 wins, 21 losses and 42 draws.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/Pakistan/Firstclass/PakistanAutomobilesCorporation/Team_Records/Playing_Record.html Pakistan Automobiles Corporation playing record]</ref> Their highest score was 201 not out by [[Ijaz Ahmed (cricketer)|Ijaz Ahmed]] against [[Karachi cricket teams|Karachi]] in 1984-85.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/Pakistan/Firstclass/PakistanAutomobilesCorporation/Batting_Records/Highest_Innings_For.html Most runs in an innings for Pakistan Automobiles Corporation]</ref> The best bowling figures were 8 for 65 by Shahid Mahboob against [[House Building Finance Corporation cricket team|House Building Finance Corporation]] in 1986-87.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/Pakistan/Firstclass/PakistanAutomobilesCorporation/Bowling_Records/Best_Innings_Bowling_For.html Most wickets in an innings for Pakistan Automobiles Corporation]</ref> He also took seven wickets in an innings for Pakistan Automobiles Corporation on seven occasions, and in 59 matches for the team took 270 wickets at an average of 27.02.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/1/1941/f_Bowling_by_Team.html Shahid Mahboob bowling for each team]</ref>
==Honours== * ''' Patron's Trophy (1) ''' * 1982-83 (not considered first-class in this season) * '''Pentangular Trophy (1) ''' * 1984-85 (not considered first-class in this season)
